Traditional bengali iftar+dinner buffet at Bhaatghor only for 650tk.
.

.
Bhaat Ghor a traditional bengali restaurant since 2019. Offers really mouthwatering bengali dishes, I tried there food before and this Ramadan they came up with iftar + dinner buffet only at 650tk with 30+ items. Bhaatghor has very simple decor but I found they will give a vibe of west bengal's restaurant. Has a seating capacity of around 30+ people. 
.
тЮбя╕П Items I tried:
1я╕ПтГг Iftar+dinner buffet: 650tk
- At their iftar+dinner buffet they are offering 30+ items where you can find deshi iftar items like chola, peyaju, beguni, alur chop, haleem, jelapi, bundia, samosa, chicken fingers, chicken lollipops and so on.  They served a pineapple salad which tastes really yummy, also there was fruits, and a very refreshing watermelon juice. I really loved the watermelon juice a lot. At dinner they offered few deshi and bangla chinese items bhaat, fried rice, soup, vegetable, achaari chicken, daal khashi, naan, chicken hariyali kabab and some other items. I just loved their daal khashi a lot it was very delicious, quite flavorful. And for desserts they offered house made mishti doi and payesh. Only 650tk for all these I would say definitely worth it. Because almost every items was tasty and I think bengali cuisines just never could go wrong. 
.
тЮбя╕П Sehri Platters:
- We were given 2 of their sehri platters too.
.
ЁЯФ╣я╕ПBeef Platter: 350tk
- Comes with bhaat, beef bhuna, daal, vegetable, 2 type of bhorta and juice. The bhortas come with these platter was just too good ЁЯШЛ.
.
ЁЯФ╕я╕ПKabab Platter: 250tk
- Hariyali kabab 2 pcs, tikka kabab or tikka butter masala 2 pcs, Naan 1 pc and juice. I always love their kababs ЁЯШД.
.
тЪая╕П This is absolutely my personal opinion. 
.
ЁЯУНPlace: Bhaatghor, 3/5 Topkhana Road, Shegunbagicha.
.

Review : Garden Gourmet by S&S Cuisineurs 
We had an informal get together last Saturday at Garden Gourmet, Bangladesh's first pop up restaurant which began operations from Dec 7, 2020 and is scheduled to close shop in March, 2021
5 bighas of space decorated in the finest decorations any event planner can provide with perfect lighting and positioning of mirrors. Love the attention to details and intricate placements of decorative items. All in all the whole restaurant space speaks of posh and spacious seating. It has this blend of modern, eclectic,  feminine as well as minimalist decorations that appeals to people with different choices. For a totally instagrammable potential, this pop up restaurant begets 10/10.
Service is topnotch. The staffs are totally cooperative and eager to assist. When we had our raffle draw, they set out chairs and arranged the prizes without any prompting and stood by until we all left in case we needed any help. During serving of meals and other requests, the other staff were equally helpful and accommodating. They always had a sincere smile on their face. In this category they deserve another 10/10 rating.
Food was ok. These are buffet meals. Reminds me of hotels and all, where the food may not be the best but they certainly are not bad either.  We were spoiled for choice as the menu was exhaustive and highly varied. I would say on average the food was tasty, given that some were great and some others were nothing special. But then given the ambience and great service, and freshly served meals, overall the food tastes good if you are dining with good company. On the whole, I will rate the food as above average.
They even have a playzone for kids as well as a spot for salah and also space for events such as birthdays and bridal showers, etc.
BOGO offers are available on certain cards. Prices are quite reasonable especially if you avail bogo for afternoon tea buffet. There are no extra or hidden charges and includes unlimited servings of food and beverages.I would highly recommend booking the venue for small family gatherings and avail the lunch+afternoon meals. The event space can be used for decorations and backdrops. One can reserve upto 300pax for such events.
They have live music and you can even request them for your special selection of songs to be sung. The acoustics were awesome, loud enough to be heard but not jarring enough to distract you from the chattings and addas. 
Covid19 measures are maintained via socially distant placements of seats and masks and sanitizers everywhere.
Note:
1. The hot beverages such as coffee and especially tea were sadly below average.
2. Deserts need to be in enclosed trays and display stands to ward off the flies and other insects, since this is an open zone.
3. I would recommend carrying mosquito repellent because despite them fumigating the place, there is a lot of mosquitoes around twilight.
